title="Linear algebra as an introduction to abstract mathematics">Linear algebra as an introduction to abstract mathematics</fr:link> Definition 9.1.1</fr:meta></fr:frontmatter><fr:mainmatter><fr:p>Let <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[\mathbb {F}]]></fr:tex> be a subfield of <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[\mathbb {C}]]></fr:tex> (possibly <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[\mathbb {F}=\mathbb {C}]]></fr:tex>). Let <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[V]]></fr:tex> be a <fr:link
type="local"
href="vectsp-000O.xml"
addr="vectsp-000O"
title="Finite-Dimensional Vector Space">Finite-Dimensional Vector Space</fr:link> over <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[\mathbb {F}]]></fr:tex>. An <html:dfn
xmlns:html="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml">Inner Product</html:dfn> on <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[V]]></fr:tex> is a map
<fr:tex
display="block"><![CDATA[\langle -,-\rangle \colon  V\times  V\to \mathbb {F}]]></fr:tex>
such that
<fr:ol><fr:li>Linearity in first slot: for all <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[u,v,w\in  V]]></fr:tex> we have <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[\langle  u+v,w\rangle =\langle  u,w\rangle +\langle  v,w\rangle ]]></fr:tex></fr:li>
<fr:li>Positivity: for all <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[v\in  V]]></fr:tex> we have <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[\langle  v,v\rangle \geq 0]]></fr:tex></fr:li>
<fr:li>Positive-definiteness: for all <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[v\in  V]]></fr:tex>, <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[\langle  v,v\rangle =0]]></fr:tex> iff <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[v=0]]></fr:tex></fr:li>
<fr:li>Conjugate symmetry: for all <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[u,v\in  V]]></fr:tex> we have <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[\langle  v,u\rangle =\overline {\langle  u,v\rangle }]]></fr:tex></fr:li></fr:ol></fr:p></fr:mainmatter><fr:backmatter /></fr:tree><fr:tree
